Puppeteer is a Node.js library that provides a high-level API to control Chrome or Chromium browsers for automation and testing. Unlike Selenium, which supports multiple browsers, Puppeteer is optimized for Chromium-based browsers. It excels in headless automation, web scraping, and generating screenshots or PDFs from web pages. Puppeteer also integrates seamlessly with modern JavaScript features and async/await.

Example Puppeteer code to scrape a webpage:
javascript
const puppeteer = require('puppeteer');

(async () => {
  const browser = await puppeteer.launch();
  const page = await browser.newPage();
  await page.goto('https://example.com');
  const title = await page.title();
  console.log('Page title:', title);
  await browser.close();
})();
